place_description: Bookseller chain stocking housebrand eReader, plus a broad selection of titles for adults & kids.

reviews_data.review_text: I love this Barnes & Noble, the staff are always so helpful with finding a particular book or recommending a new read.
Muy buen lugar muy agradable
Peaceful

Customer service is godawful here maybe don't imply your customers can't afford a membership when they tell you they don't have one. I literally only come here for books that's aren't available on kindle unlimited I won't benefit from a membership. Came in 4/3 and was checked but by Humberto proceeds to ask if I have a membership and j say no. Asks if I want a bag and I say yes (it is pouring rain outside) and he says oh sorry bags are only for members and it's raining outside sorry about your book. Then proceeds to say because I'm a nice guy I'll give you a bag I know it's the first of the month and people have bills to pay. EXCUSE ME??? I get that you get bonuses for selling memberships but god bless maybe don't insinuate I can't afford it.
Clean store good selection
That distinct smell of books!!!! I could spend hours here. Two stories of amazing!!!

I have not been I am book store in years, when I walked in Barnes in Noble to find a particular book I felt overwhelmed, I asked a gentleman for helping me and he was so kind and patient! Thank you for helping me to experience the joy of a book store again! Will definitely be back!
Love the shop and all they books and albums and sweet employees
I love coming here, staff are very nice and helpful. Variety of books to choose from, love it!

Disappointed they stopped selling many of the humor books I used to buy from them but still a great place to go and chill and read. I bought a Prince picture disk album and two dvds and one book for my collection of Calvin and Hobbes. I will be returning.
Great
Nice inventory of books, collectibles, magazines, toys, vinyls, novelty items, music, and movies. Courteous and considerate staff.

The kinds of things put on display, especially near kids is super sketchy. It's really sad because it wasnt always like this. I used to love this place as a kid, and I'm sad I now get nervous taking my own in here.
Very nice! Clean and lots of open space to get a drink and read your books. Might bring headphones to block out the kids.

Making inquiries about their rewards programs and various emails I receive from them. Also inquired about making the best use of the eReader I purchased from them. I may as well have been on Mars. And they are sooooo helpful when you're making a purchase.
I love this kingdom of books. It was amazing experience for me. Its open hundreds of horizons to my eyes.
I love the cafe so much I eat there even when I'm not ordering from there!
Bookstores are getting hard to find these days. This Barnes and Noble is like a bookstore mall. So many sections filled to the brim with the latest books and some classics too.

I'm so like their change to a more local bookstore feel. A great place to come and spend the day drinking something and reading. Especially with the food court right outside I need not even leave the area, though it nice to walk around and stretch my legs around the mall now and then. The workers are friendly and provide book recommendations. I am do happy real book stores survive. Also great vinyl record selection.
The staff was very helpful and everything we were trying to find was easily located.
Love this location, everyone's so friendly and helpful!

My favorite Barnes & Noble's location! Extremely friendly staff and knowledgeable team!
thank you
Love the new place!! We were so disappointed when the old one closed. Thank goodness foe the new store

The cashiers here are top tier and honest with me every time I show up looking for a last minute gift. They are so professional. When you come here it feels like a family owned business in a small town rather than a chain. Everyone treats it like it's their business.

Everything you can imagine, book wise, is here! From fun books for the kids, to informative, to step by step recipe books! It's not all fiction or a bunch of scholastic book fair junk but actually really nice and helpful
Excellent selection
Awesome book store!
The cashier Humberto (i think) was very kind and helpful.
Cashier just keep talking talking

Great service! They make sure I get online price matching for the best deals and help me find any item I am seeking.

One of the last bookstores with new books in it. They have more toys and miscellaneous items since last time I was in a Barnes and Nobel but most related to novels. If you like coffee there is a Starbucks and plenty of seating.
When you are looking for relaxation and quiet time to read that special book or books; rest well and enjoy that moment.
Great place

They have 2 big upholstered chairs upstairs and several downstairs. I was at the mall with my 4 of my grandchildren and planned to hang here while they did their thing. I got food from McAlister deli in the mall and ate it in the Starbucks in Barnes and Noble!!
Love it. Big store, two stories. Books, magazines, coffee,  and more. Looks like they have a great selection of books and games.
Great location. Nice employees. Large selection of physical ;which in a digital world is nice to see.

When I walked in, I was overwhelmed by the selection, I felt like I was in a truly 5 Star Pl. They have three floors, where the first floor is where the children's toys and adult games are. There is something for everyone in your family, to buy for your friends. Just a wonderful experience overall. One and then go upstairs to find fiction and nonfiction alike, sit down for coffee and dessert, and even tasteful dishes healthy sandwiches. If everyone wants to enhancer experience, they can join to be a premier member, after which they receive 10% of all titles in addition to discounts on the food. The parkingis perfect, and there is handicap accessibility.
Some of the prices are high, even with 10%, it's much of a discount.  But I like the people that work there.
Worn out, desperately needs to be refurbished.

Overpriced

I love a good bookstore... And this place never disappoints! Of course, you need to have a couple of hours to really browse through. But the associates are so helpful. This book store earns a 5 star rating mainly because it exists.  Most brick and mortar book stores have gone the way of the dodo. Nice open floor plan to peruse the store I had come like always come to the mall with a sense of uneasiness to shop for a new Funko Pop LLC for collection.  Easy to find displayed neatly in order. I asked for a price check on a common mandalorian Fenic Shand priced 11.99 normally appraised around 8.00 so naturally I had to ask the lovely lady for a quick check and she did so with no "snappy it should be on the box " like  most employees answer nowadays .  It  was naturally the price on the box but still she more than willing to assist me with this small issue with a smile she knew it wouldn't be on sale yet because I had asked her about this she was very good about a silly question from a silly collector.  she even apologized for the price of the little toy and I was truly caught off guard by the sorry . We wanted to learn more about upgrading to the newer Nook electronic reader.  Unfortunately, the staff didn't know much about the Nook - and repeatedly gave inaccurate information (clearly they hadn't even read the marketing material and were just winging it).  We had made a trip into the store to talk with someone about the product and get another perspective than the online reviews (which are very mixed) and we were definitely disappointed and spent our time doing the teaching - would have been better if they just said that they didn't know anything about the Nook product.  I guess we will need to just stick with online reviews.
Don't go to the Starbucks here. Manager acts like he is better than everyone else and is disrespectful. He works really slowly and takes his time. He also doesn't make the drinks correctly.

So many different types of notebooks, daily planners, even tho thus day and age with electronics keeping our schedules for us, it's always nice to have a beautiful notebook,  and write things down in. Many books, in so many different forms of reading them, collectable, like funko pops, little knic knacks, pens, book marks, I can go on and on!! Please visit the Barnes and noble website,  you won't be disappointed!

The staff here at Barnes and Noble are super helpful.  We saw a book when we first walked in, and we planned to buy it on our way back out of the mall, but it was gone two hours later. Worst experience I've ever had at a Barnes & Noble bookstore! The employee Tim was rude, disrespectful, and unprofessional during my visit. I came in to complete a exchange for some books and Tim immediately was rude and threatened to call security on me because I didn't have the proper documentation. Instead of explaining the policy to me and telling what I needed for this exchange, he just said no and threatened me with security. His manager then came and asked him to leave and go to the back. He then began to argue and go back and forth with me in front of customers and his coworkers. He was trying to justify why acted the way he did. I've never experienced any this ever at this store. I recommend all customers to go to any other Barnes and Noble besides this one. Again his name is Tim.
